---
import Layout from '../layouts/TaskRocketLayout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Messaging Compliance | TaskRocket" description="TaskRocket opt-in and messaging compliance policy.">
  <section class="legal"><div class="container"><article><h1>Messaging Compliance / Opt-In Policy</h1><p>TaskRocket only sends SMS messages to users who opt in through the TaskRocket website form.</p><h2>Opt-In Workflow</h2><p>Users opt in by completing the TaskRocket Free Workflow Review form and checking the optional SMS consent checkbox. The checkbox is unchecked by default and consent is not required to purchase services.</p><h2>Message Purpose</h2><p>Messages may relate to the user's inquiry, workflow review, demo request, scheduling, service updates, and account communication.</p><h2>Opt-Out and Help</h2><p>Users can reply STOP to unsubscribe or HELP for help.</p><h2>Privacy</h2><p>SMS consent is not sold or shared with third parties for marketing purposes.</p><h2>Twilio Verification Description</h2><p>Users opt in by completing the TaskRocket Free Workflow Review form on taskrocket.org. The form includes an optional SMS consent checkbox that is unchecked by default. The checkbox states that by checking it, the user consents to receive text messages from TaskRocket related to their inquiry, workflow review, demo request, scheduling, service updates, and account communication. Consent is not a condition of purchase. The form links to the Privacy Policy and SMS Terms & Conditions. Users can reply STOP to unsubscribe or HELP for help.</p></article></div></section>
</Layout>
